{"key":"processedPost-11862966","value":{"id":11862966,"first":11862322,"last":11862966,"when":1263965419,"utime":"01/20/10 07:30 AM","content":"Untape the holes.&nbsp; Fresh air is the number one pinning trigger and far more important than the humidity most new growers think is king.&nbsp; In addition, you're going to be misting four or five times per day.&nbsp; There's no way you won't have proper humidity if your ambient is 40%, which is actually pretty high during winter.<br /><br />Another tip is to rake your fingers through the perlite to rake it and fluff it up.&nbsp; If it's packed down or level, there's not as much surface area to evaporate water.&nbsp; Make sure you've calibrated your hygrometer via the damp towel method.&nbsp; Hopefully, you put holes in all six sides.&nbsp; The holes in the bottom are especially important for maintaining proper humidity.<br />RR","title":"Re: My first grow, shotgun terrarium humidity/FAE questions","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}